                  <summary/>
            
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1763Legend">Ṣalot za-qǝddus Susǝnyos baʾǝnta ʾasassǝlo dawe</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        <supplied reason="lost">በ</supplied>ስመ፡ አብ፡ <gap reason="omitted" extent="unknown" resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices"/>  ጸሎት፡ 
                        በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ሾተላይ፡ ባርያ፡ ወደም፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ሱስንዮስ፡ በስመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ሕያው፡ ነባቢ፡ ወተናጋሪ፡ ጸሎት፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ሱስንዮስ፡ በእንተ፡ <del rend="effaced">አ</del>ሰስሎ፡ ደቄ፡ 
                        እምሕፃና<del rend="effaced">ት</del>፡ እለ፡ 
                           <sic>ይጠብው፡</sic>
                         ጥበ፡ <supplied reason="lost">እ</supplied>ሞሙ፡ ይበቍዕ፡ 
                        ሎሙ፡ ረድኤተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ልዑል፡ ወክቡር፡ ጸሎቱ፡ ወበረከቱ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሱስንዮስ፡ የሃሉ፡ ምስለ፡ <supplied reason="lost">አ</supplied>መቱ፡ ወለተ፡    
                        <add place="overstrike">መድ<supplied reason="omitted">ኅን፡</supplied>
                        </add> ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። ወሀሎ፡ ፩ብእሲ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ሱስንዮስ፡ ወአውሰበ፡ ብእሲተ፡ 
                        ወወለ<supplied reason="lost">ደ</supplied>ት፡ ወልደ፡ 
                           <sic>ወወልተ፡</sic>
                         
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="gez">
                        ወበ፯ሊቃነ፡ መላእክት፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወገብርኤል፡ ሱራፌል፡ ወኪሩቤል፡ ኡራኤል፡ ወሩፋኤል፡ ወፋኑኤል፡ ሰዳካኤል፡ አናንያል፡ እሉ፡ እሙንቱ፡ እለ፡ ይቀውሙ፡ ቅድመ፡ እግዚአ<supplied reason="lost">ብ</supplied>ሔር፡ 
                        አኃዜ፡ ኵሉ፡ ዘልፈ፡ እስከ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ጸሎቱ፡ ወበረከቱ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሱስንዮስ፡ የሃሉ፡ ምስለ፡ ዓመቱ፡ ወለተ፡ <add place="overstrike">መድኅን፡</add>
                     </explicit>
                     <note>The name of a later owner of the scroll, <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11645WalattaM">Walatta Madḫǝn</persName>, is written over another 
                     erased name in the supplication formulas at the beginning and at the end of the text.</note>
                  </msItem> 
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4643Salam">Malkǝʾ-hymn to St Susǝnyos</title>
                     <note>
                        The text is followed by a short invocation: <q xml:lang="gez">ኦአምላክ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ሱስንዮስ፡ አድኅኖ፡ እምሕማመ፡ ሾተላይ፡ ባርያ፡ በላዕለ፡ ዓመትከ፡ ወለተ፡</q>. The last 
                        name is partly erased, only Walatta is legible.
                     </note>
                   </msItem>  
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                     <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4644MagicPr">Ṣalot baʾənta ḥəmāma ʿāynat bāryā wa-ʿāyna sabʾ ʾəkuy
          wa-legewon</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        በስመ፡ አብ፡ <gap reason="omitted" extent="unknown" resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices"/> ጸሎት፡ በንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ዓይነት፡ ባርያ፡ ወዓይነ፡ ሰብእ፡ እኩይ፡ 
                        ወሌጌዎን፡ አስማተ፡ ሰሎሞን፡ ዘረበቦሙ፡ ለዓጋንንት፡ ከመ፡ 
                           <sic>መርበበተ፡</sic>
                         ዓሣ፡ ዘውስተ፡ ባሕር፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፡ 
                        ሰዱስ<del rend="erasure">ቃ</del>ኤል፡ ሰዱቃኤል፡ ሰዱቃኤል፡
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="gez">
                        ከማሁ፡ አድኅኖ፡ እምሕማመ፡ ሾተላይ፡ ባርያ፡ በላዕለ፡ ዓመትከ፡ ወለተ፡ <add place="overstrike">መድኅን፡</add>
                     </explicit>
                     <note>The name of a later owner of the scroll, <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11645WalattaM">Walatta Madḫǝn</persName>, is written over another 
                        erased name in the supplication formula at the end of the text.</note>
                  </msItem>       
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i4">
                     <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4645MagicPr">Ṣalot baʾənta ḥəmāma šotalāy bāryā wa-mafarrəg</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ሾተላይ፡ ባርያ፡ ወመ<del rend="erasure">ፈ</del>ርግ<gap reason="illegible"/>፡ ሰየ፡ ሰየ፡ ሰየ፡ ሰሃ፡ ሰሃ፡ ሰሃ፡
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="gez">
                        በኃይለ፡ ዝንቱ፡ <unclear>አስማት፡</unclear> ለዓመትከ፡ ወ<supplied reason="lost">ለተ፡</supplied> መድኀ<supplied reason="lost">ን፡</supplied> 
                        <gap reason="illegible"/> ለእግዚእ።
                     </explicit>
                     <note>The text is preceded by an ornamental diagram with eight sections. 
                        The name of a later owner of the scroll, <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11645WalattaM">Walatta Madḫǝn</persName>, is written in the 
                        supplication formula at the end of the text.</note>
                  </msItem>    
